This paper discusses the issue of inferring users' true preferences in the context of HCI research, which is closely related to the field of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also touches upon the topic of cognitive biases, which is relevant to the field of cybernetics (cs.CY) and social and information networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of metrics to optimize products, which is relevant to the fields of computational complexity (cs.CC) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
